org.md2k.datakitapi.status

Class Status

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.md2k.datakitapi.status.Status
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    android.os.Parcelable

    public class Status
extends java.lang.Object
implements android.os.Parcelable
    This class creates a status object that contains details about the current operational status of the application.

    Possible statuses and their keys are:

    • SUCCESS, key = 0
    • DATASOURCE_EXIST, key = 1
    • DATASOURCE_MULTIPLE_EXIST, key = 2
    • DATASOURCE_NOT_EXIST, key = 3
    • DATASOURCE_INVALID, key = 4
    • DATASOURCE_ACTIVE, key = 5
    • INTERNAL_ERROR, key = -3
    • ALREADY_SUBSCRIBED, key = 7
    • ERROR_NOT_INSTALLED, key = -1
    • ERROR_BOUND, key = -2
    • DATA_INVALID, key = 8
